/mf addlaw - Add a law to your faction.
/mf ally - Attempt to ally with a faction.
/mf autoclaim - Toggle auto claim, making land claiming easier.
/mf breakalliance - Break an alliance with a faction.
/mf checkaccess - Check who has access to a locked block.
/mf checkclaim - Check if land is claimed.
/mf claim - Claim land for your faction.
/mf config set (option) (value) - Set a config value.
/mf declareindependence - Declare independence from your liege.
/mf declarewar - Declare war against another faction.
/mf demote - Demote an officer to member status.
/mf disband - Disband your faction (must be owner).
/mf editlaw - Edit an already existing law in your faction.
/mf force - Force the plugin to perform certain actions.
/mf grantaccess - Grant someone access to a locked block.
/mf grantindependence - Grant a vassal vaction independence.
/mf help # - Show lists of useful commands.
/mf home - Teleport to your faction home.
/mf info - See your faction or another faction's information.
/mf invite (player) - Invite a player to your faction.
/mf invoke (ally) (enemy) - Call an allied faction into a war.
/mf join (faction) - Join a faction if you've been invited.
/mf kick - Kick a player from your faction.
/mf laws - View the laws of your faction.
/mf list - List all factions on the server.
/mf lock - Lock a chest or door.
/mf makepeace - Send peace offer to another faction.
/mf members - List the members of your faction or another faction.
/mf promote - Promote a player to officer status.
/mf removelaw - Remove a law from your faction.
/mf resetpowerlevels - Reset player power records and faction cumulative power levels.
/mf revokeaccess - Revoke someone's access to a locked block.
/mf swearfealty - Swear fealty to a faction.
/mf transfer - Transfer ownership of your faction to another player.\n
/mf unclaim - Unclaim land for your faction.
/mf unclaimall - Unclaim all land for your faction.
/mf unlock Unlock a chest or door.
/mf vassalize - Offer to vassalize a faction.
/mf who - View the faction info a specific player.
